hopobject.body: Good crew it's cool :) how much does celexa cost in canada But it still feels as if the old divide between the vulgar and the pedantic – or “yobs and w-----s”, as Kingsley Amis christened them – is growing wider than ever. On one side are those who can use phrases like “totes amazeballs” or “whatever” (voted America’s most annoying word for the past four years) and not feel a flicker of shame. On the other are those who recoil from artificial informality – who shudder at having their first name used by letter-writers and cold-callers. Instead of Roundheads and Cavaliers, or Eloi and Morlocks, we’re split between Tus and Vous.
